# .gitignore - Zero-Trust Allowlist
#
# Philosophy: deny everything by default, then allowlist intentionally.
# Each un-ignored path is here on purpose, not by accident. A contributor
# who drops a .env, key, token, or credential anywhere in the tree finds
# it ignored, not tracked.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Deny everything first
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
*
/**
/.*
/.*/
.DS_Store

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Global sensitive-file protection (before allowlist; belt-only,
#    the re-exclusions in section 5 are the real guard)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Env files
.env
.env.*
!.env.template
!.env.example
!.env.sample

# Keys and certs
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
*.der
*.asc
*.gpg
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*_rsa
*_ed25519

# Generic secret markers
*.secret
*.secrets
secrets.json
secrets.yaml
credentials.json
**/secrets/

# Cloud credentials
.aws/
.azure/
.gcloud/
gcloud-key.json
service-account*.json
firebase-adminsdk*.json

# History and token files
.netrc
.npmrc
.pypirc
.bash_history
.zsh_history
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/

# Dump / backup leaks
*.sql
*.dump
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Allowlisted project content
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Add !path/ and !path/** pairs for every folder the project tracks.
# Never use a bare !folder/ without !folder/** - git will not recurse
# into an ignored parent without both lines.

# Repo / meta
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!README.md
!AGENTS.md
!CLAUDE.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md

# CI/CD
!.github/
!.github/**

# docs/ - project wiki SSOT (see docs-ssot.md)
!docs/
!docs/**

# .atlas/ - atlas's own auditable operational state (see docs-ssot.md).
# .atlas/.run/ is ephemeral and re-excluded in section 4 below.
# The directory entry itself must be un-ignored first (no trailing slash,
# so it is a traversal-only rule, not a !.atlas/** blanket) so git can
# recurse into it at all - a parent directory left excluded blocks every
# nested allow rule below it, no matter how specific.
!.atlas
!.atlas/evidence/
!.atlas/evidence/**
!.atlas/findings/
!.atlas/findings/**
!.atlas/audits/
!.atlas/audits/**
!.atlas/decisions/
!.atlas/decisions/**
!.atlas/archive/
!.atlas/archive/**
!.atlas/understand-anything/
!.atlas/understand-anything/**
!.atlas/graphify/
!.atlas/graphify/**
!.atlas/self-improvement/
!.atlas/self-improvement/**
!.atlas/memory/
!.atlas/memory/**
!.atlas/nudge/
!.atlas/nudge/**
!.atlas/CLAUDE.md
!.atlas/AGENTS.md

# --- project-specific allowlist entries go here ---

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Re-exclude ephemeral atlas run state (MUST come after allowlist,
#    so it wins over the .atlas/ allowlist above; only the durable
#    findings ledger is re-included)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Un-ignore the .run directory entry itself first (no trailing slash,
# traversal-only - the bare top-level "*" in section 1 would otherwise
# keep it excluded), then glob its contents rather than the directory,
# then re-include the one durable file. Git cannot re-include a file
# whose parent directory is excluded, so skipping either step above
# would make the findings.json negation below a silent no-op.
!.atlas/.run
.atlas/.run/*
!.atlas/.run/findings.json

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Re-exclude generated artifacts (MUST come after allowlist)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Node / TypeScript
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.next/
**/.nuxt/
**/.cache/
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/coverage/

# Python
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv/
**/.venv.nosync.noindex/
**/venv/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/

# Per-folder env re-exclusions (one block per tracked app)
# frontend/.env
# frontend/.env.*
# !frontend/.env.example

# OS / editor noise
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
!**/.vscode/settings.json.example
**/*.swp

# Synced-drive artifacts (uncomment if the stack uses iCloud / Dropbox)
# **/*.nosync*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. Pre-commit verification footer
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Pre-commit verification:
#   1. git status                                 # nothing unexpected staged?
#   2. git check-ignore -v .env                   # confirm secrets are ignored
#   3. git ls-files | grep -E '\.(env|key|pem)$'  # confirm no secrets tracked
#   4. git diff --cached                          # review staged content
# If ANY secret-like file appears in steps 1, 3, or 4 - STOP and investigate.